So I found a suitable container, BoxLayout.

Description of containers here:
http://java.sun.com/products/jfc/tsc/articles/containers/#swing_containers

"Repurporsed" the example code:
http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/uiswing/examples/layout/BoxAlignmentDemoProject/src/layout/BoxAlignmentDemo.java

Which is described here:
http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/uiswing/layout/box.html

And finally used this "in-line" HTML "hack" to make both the tabs and buttons bigger:
http://weblogs.java.net/blog/xuanyun/archive/2009/01/change_the_tab_1.html Heh, had to do this before to format bash output using PHP.


